notes.text:
This update for ImageMagick fixes the following issues:

Security issues fixed:

- CVE-2019-11597: Fixed a heap-based buffer over-read in the WriteTIFFImage() (bsc#1138464).
- Fixed a file content disclosure via SVG and WMF decoding (bsc#1138425).

notes.text: In ImageMagick 7.0.8-43 Q16, there is a heap-based buffer over-read in the function WriteTIFFImage of coders/tiff.c, which allows an attacker to cause a denial of service or possibly information disclosure via a crafted image file.
